From: José Augusto de Lima Prestes <doutorprestes@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Fix user config ignored when project config exists

Vibe CLI was ignoring ~/.vibe/config.toml when a project-level
.vibe/config.toml existed. User-defined [[models]] and active_model
were silently discarded.

  - HarnessFilesManager: moved user_config_file property next to
    config_file for discoverability (path stays ~/.vibe/config.toml,
    NOT ~/.vibe/.vibe/config.toml — the .vibe/ subdirectory is a
    project-level convention)
  - TomlFileSettingsSource._load_toml(): merge user + project configs
    with user taking precedence
  - _deep_merge_preserving_lists(): intelligent merge for models and
    providers lists by identifier (alias / name)

This patch is a derivative work of Mistral Vibe, Copyright Mistral AI.
Original: https://github.com/mistralai/mistral-vibe (Apache 2.0)
Signed-off-by: José Augusto de Lima Prestes <doutorprestes@gmail.com>

